Eleven suspected kidnappers of the Mr John Mamman, the Special Adviser on Local Government, Chieftaincy Affairs and Community Development, has been arrested by police. The commissioner of Police in Nasarawa state, Bola Longe Emmanuel, confirmed the arrests of the suspects to journalists in his office in Lafia. According to him, one person was arrested on the day of the kidnap, while seven others were arrested in connection with the kidnapped, while three were engaged in a shoot out with police. Longe, said since the abduction of the special adviser, the police mounted a tight security surveillance and condoned the area. He said the command deployed tactical strategies, which included men of the Special Anti Robeery squad, Mobile force as well as air survelaince to cordoned the flash points in the state. “We launched an intense pressure on the kidnappers, who according to information were at a village along Doma community. “They could not help but released Mr John Mammam, as we later arrested three other suspected who our men engaged them on a shootout, but one escaped, while among the two arrested, one of them was badly wounded ” Longe said. Meanwhile, the Kidnapped victim said he has forgiven his kidnappers “for they don’t they know what they are doing” “I have forgiven them and I pray they they will repent of their sins. I don’t pray any of my friends and relations to be their victim” he said Mammann, who spoke to our correspondent in his residence in Garaku, yesterday, expressed gratitude God and all those who stood by him during his trail moment. Mamman, who is the Special Adviser on Local Government, Chieftaincy Affairs and Community Development was freed on Tuesday Night. It would be recalled that he was kidnapped on Saturday evening in his house at Dari, in kokona Local Government Area of the state.